{"word":"λαός","slug":"λαός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>λαός, οῦ, ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ orig.\">orig.</a> unknown] ‘a group of humans’, <b>people<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> of <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pers.\">pers.</a> gathered in an area or place <b><a href='B:490 1:10'>Lk 1:10</a>; <a href='B:490 3:15'>3:15</a>; <a href='B:490 6:17'>6:17</a>; <a href='B:510 3:9'>Ac 3:9</a>; <a href='B:510 4:1'>4:1</a>; <a href='B:510 10:2'>10:2</a>; <a href='B:510 21:40'>21:40</a>; <a href='B:530 10:7'>1 Cor 10:7</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> of people groups understood geographically or ethnically <b><a href='B:730 5:9'>Rv 5:9</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>c.</pp></b> of people groups associated with God, including <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ esp.\">esp.</a> traditional Israel <b><a href='B:470 1:21'>Mt 1:21</a>; <a href='B:490 2:10'>Lk 2:10</a>; <a href='B:500 11:50'>J 11:50</a>; <a href='B:510 3:23'>Ac 3:23</a>; <a href='B:510 10:2'>10:2</a>; <a href='B:520 11:1'>Ro 11:1</a>; <a href='B:540 6:16'>2 Cor 6:16</a>; <a href='B:630 2:14'>Tit 2:14</a>; <a href='B:650 2:17'>Hb 2:17</a></b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ oft.\">oft.</a> in Hb; <b><a href='B:670 2:9'>1 Pt 2:9</a>; <a href='B:680 2:1'>2 Pt 2:1</a>; <a href='B:720 1:1'>Jd 5</a>; <a href='B:730 18:4'>Rv 18:4</a>; <a href='B:730 21:3'>21:3</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Λαοδικεύς\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:λάρυγξ\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}